  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  sourcePage 2
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line 2
  line `THE AFRICAN DEVELOPMENT FUND ACT, 1982`
  line `A CT N O. 1 OF 1982`
  line `[4 th March, 1982.]`
  line `An Act to implement the African Development Fund Agreement and for matters connected`
  line therewith.
  line `B E it enacted by Parliament in the Thirty-third Year of the Republic of India as follows: —`
  line `1. Short title, extent and commencement. — ( 1 ) This Act may be called the African Development`
  line `Fund Act, 1982.`
  line `( 2 ) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line `( 3 ) It shall come into force on such date 1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
  line `2. Definitions. — In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “ Agreement ” means the African Development Fund Agreement;`
  line `( b ) “ Fund ” means the African Development Fund established under the Agreement.`
  line `3. Payments to Fund. — ( 1 )There shall be paid out of the Consolidated Fund of India, after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, all such sums as may, from time to time, be`
  line `required for the purpose of paying, —`
  line `( a ) the subscription payable by the Central Government to the Fund under Articles 6,7,8 and 9 of`
  line `the Agreement;`
  line `( b ) any sums payable by the Central Government to the Fund under Article 13 of the Agreement;`
  line and
  line `( c ) any charges payable by the Central Government to the Fund under Article 16 of the`
  line Agreement.
  line `( 2 ) The Central Government may, if it thinks fit so to do, create and issue to the Fund, in such form as`
  line `it thinks fit, any such non-interest bearing and non-negotiable note or other obligations as are provided for`
  line `by Article 9 of the Agreement.`
  line `4. Reserve Bank to be depository for Fund. — The Reserve Bank of India shall be the depository of`
  line `the Indian currency holdings of the Fund.`
  line `5. Conferment of status and certain immunities, exemptions and privileges on Fund and`
  line `conferment of certain immunities, exemptions and privileges on its officers and`
  line `employees. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any other law, the provisions of`
  line `the Agreement set out in the Schedule shall have the force of law in India:`
  line `Provided that nothing in Article 49 of the Agreement shall be construed as —`
  line `( a ) entitling the Fund to import into India goods free of any duty of customs without any`
  line `restriction or their subsequent sale therein; or`
  line `( b ) conferring on the Fund any exemption from duties or taxes which form part of the price of`
  line `goods sold; or`
  line `( c ) conferring on the Fund any exemption from duties or taxes which are in fact no more than`
  line `charges for services rendered.`
  line `1. 25thAugust, 1986, vide notification No. G.S.R. 1035(E), dated 25th August, 1986, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3( i ).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-3
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Page 3`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  sourcePage 3
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line 3
  line `( 2 ) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, amend the Schedule in`
  line `conformity with any amendments, duly made and adopted, of the provisions of the Agreement set out`
  line therein.
  line `6. Power to make rules. — The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line `7. Notifications issued under section 5 and rules made under section 6 to be laid before`
  line `Parliament. — Every notification issued under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 5 and every rule made under`
  line `section 6 shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is issued or made, before each House of Parliament,`
  line `while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or`
  line `more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the notification or, as the`
  line `case may be, in the rule or both Houses agree that the notification or rule should not be issued or made,`
  line `the notification or rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the`
  line `case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the`
  line `validity of anything previously done under that notification or rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-4
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Page 4`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  sourcePage 4
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line 4
  line `THE SCHEDULE`
  line `( See section 5)`
  line `PROVISIONS OF THE AGREEMENT WHICH SHALL HAVE FORCE OF LAW`
  line `CHAPTER VIII`
  line `S TATUS, I MMUNITIES, E XEMPTIONSAND P RIVILEGES`
  line `ARTICLE 41`
  line `P URPOSE OF C HAPTER`
  line `To enable the Fund effectively to fulfil its purpose and carry out the functions entrusted to it, the`
  line `status, immunities, exemptions and privileges set forth in this Chapter shall be accorded to the Fund in the`
  line `territory of each State participant, and each State participant shall inform the Fund of the specific action`
  line `which it has taken for such purpose.`
  line `ARTICLE 42`
  line `S TATUS`
  line `The Fund shall possess full judicial personality and, in particular, full capacity:`
  line `( i ) to contract;`
  line `( ii ) to acquire, and dispose of, immovable and movable property; and`
  line `( iii ) to institute legal proceedings.`
  line `ARTICLE 43`
  line `L EGAL P ROCESS`
  line `1. The Fund shall enjoy immunity from every form of legal process, except in cases arising out of or`
  line `in connection with the exercise of its power to receive loans in accordance with Article 8, in which case`
  line `actions may be brought against the Fund in a court of competent jurisdiction in the territory of a country`
  line `in which the Fund has its office, or has appointed an agent for the purpose of accepting service or notice`
  line `of process, or has otherwise agreed to be sued.`
  line `2. Notwithstanding the provisions of paragraph 1, no action shall be brought against the Fund by any`
  line `participant, or by any agency or instrumentality of a participant, or by any entity or person directly or`
  line `indirectly acting for or deriving claims from a participant or from any agency or instrumentality of a`
  line `participant. Participants shall have recourse to such special procedures for the settlement of disputes`
  line `between the Fund and its participants as may be prescribed in this Agreement, in the bye-laws and`
  line `regulations of the Fund, or in contracts entered into with the Fund.`
  line `3. The Fund shall also make provision for appropriate modes of settlement of disputes in cases which`
  line `do not come within the provisions of paragraph 2 and of Articles 52 and 53 and which are subject to the`
  line `immunity of the Fund by virtue of paragraph 1 of this Article.`
  line `4. Where by virtue of any of the provisions of this Agreement the Fund does not enjoy immunity`
  line `from legal process, the Fund, and its property and assets wherever located and by whomsoever held, shall`
  line `nevertheless be immune from all forms of seizure, attachment or execution before the delivery of final`
  line `judgment against the Fund.`
  line `ARTICLE 44`
  line `I MMUNITY OF A SSETS`
  line `Property and assets of the Fund, wherever located and by whomsoever held, shall be immune from`
  line `search, requisition, confiscation, expropriation or any other form of taking or foreclosure by executive or`
  line `legislative action.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-5
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Page 5`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  sourcePage 5
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line 5
  line `ARTICLE 45`
  line `I MMUNITY OF A RCHIVES`
  line `The archives of the Fund, and, in general, all documents belonging to it or held by it, shall be`
  line `inviolable, wherever located.`
  line `ARTICLE 46`
  line `F REEDOM OF A SSETS FROM R ESTRICTION`
  line `To the extent necessary to carry out the purpose and function of the Fund, and subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Agreement, all property and other assets of the Fund shall be free from restriction by`
  line `financial controls, regulations, or moratoria of any kind.`
  line `ARTICLE 47`
  line `P RIVILEGE FOR C OMMUNICATIONS`
  line `Official communications of the Fund shall be accorded by each State participant the same treatment`
  line `as it accords to the official communications of other international financial institutions of which it is a`
  line member.
  line `ARTICLE 48`
  line `I MMUNITIES AND P RIVILEGES OF O FFICIALS AND P ERSONNEL`
  line `All governors and directors, and their alternates, the President and personnel, including experts`
  line `performing missions for the Fund:`
  line `( i ) shall be immune from legal process with respect to acts performed by them in their official`
  line capacity;
  line `( ii ) when they are not local nationals, shall be accorded no less favourable immunities from`
  line `immigration restrictions, alien registration requirements and national service obligations, and no less`
  line `favourable facilities as regards exchange regulations, than are accorded by the State participant`
  line `concerned to the representatives, officials and employees of comparable rank of any other`
  line `international financial institution of which it is a member; and`
  line `( iii ) shall be granted no less favourable treatment in respect of travelling facilities than is`
  line `accorded by the State participant concerned to representatives, officials and employees of comparable`
  line `rank of any other international financial institution of which it is a member.`
  line `ARTICLE 49`
  line `E XEMPTION FROM T AXATION`
  line `1. The Fund, its assets, property, income, operations and transactions, shall be exempt from all direct`
  line `taxation, and from all customs duties, or taxes having equivalent effect, on goods imported or exported`
  line `for its official use. The Fund shall also be exempt from any obligation for the payment, withholding or`
  line `collection of any tax or duty.`
  line `2. Notwithstanding the provisions of paragraph 1, the Fund shall not claim exemption from taxes`
  line `which are no more than charges for services rendered.`
  line `3. Articles imported under an exemption provided for by paragraph 1 shall not be sold in the territory`
  line `of the State participant which granted the exemption except under conditions agreed with that participant.`
  line `4. No tax shall be levied on or in respect of salaries and emoluments paid by the Fund to the President`
  line `and personnel including experts performing missions for it.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-6
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Page 6`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  sourcePage 6
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line 6
  line `ARTICLE 50`
  line `W AIVER BY THE F UND`
  line `1. The immunities, exemptions and privileges provided in this Chapter are granted in the interests of`
  line `the Fund. The Board of Directors may waive, to such extent and upon such conditions as it may`
  line `determine, the immunities, exemptions and privileges provided in this Chapter in cases where its action`
  line `would in its opinion further the interests of the Fund.`
  line `2. Regardless of the provisions of paragraph 1, the President shall have the right and the duty to waive`
  line `the immunity of any of the personnel, including experts performing missions for the Fund, in cases where,`
  line `in his opinion, the immunity would impede the course of justice and can be waived without prejudice to`
  line `the interests of the Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
